  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0bae\u0bc8\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0bb5\u0bc0\u0b9f\u0bc1 \u0bb0\u0ba3\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 !",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Maithri's house for Ranil!",
      "author": "Vishnu",
      "body_lines": [
        "It has been decided to give the current President Ranil Wickremesinghe a house located in Paget Road, Colombo, which was used as his official residence by the former President and Member of Parliament Maithripala Sirisena during his presidency.",
        "It is said that the Presidential Palace and Alari Palace have been damaged in the background where lakhs of people visited after they were captured by the protesters.",
        "In this situation, while legal actions and rectification work are being carried out in relation to these houses, it has become impossible for the President or the Prime Minister to visit them.",
        "In this situation, President Ranil Wickremesinghe's personal residence has also been damaged by fire, and he is currently being kept in a safe place under the full protection of the security forces.",
        "In this situation, temporarily, the government has decided to give the Beget Street house to President Ranil.",
        "On March 29th, the High Court issued an interim injunction against the decision taken by the cabinet to allow Maithripala Sirisena to own the house located on Paget Road, Colombo, which was used as his official residence during the presidency of Maithripala Sirisena, after his retirement from office and continuing.",
        "Following this, former President Maithripala Sirisena came out of his house located on Paget Road, Colombo.",
        "The interim injunction was issued by a bench of judges headed by Justice Preethi Padman Surasena and comprising Justices Yasanda Gotakoda and Mahinda Samayawardana.",
        "This interim injunction was issued with effect from four weeks from the date of issue, March 29.",
        "As the former president was unable to continue staying at the Paget Road house, he has announced that he will leave the house after the New Year.",
        "Former President Maithripala Sirisena has moved out of his Paget Street house and is staying in a new house even as the government has given him another house in Colombo.",
        "This fundamental rights violation petition has been filed by the Center for Alternative Policies and its Executive Director Pakhyasothi Saravanamuthu, demanding that the decision taken by the Cabinet to make the house located on Paget Road, the property of the former President Maithripala Sirisena, after his retirement from the presidency, is a violation of basic human rights.",
        "Former President Maithripala Sirisena and current cabinet members have been named as respondents to the petition.",
        "It is noteworthy that the Presidents' Rights Act No. 4 of 1986 provides housing for retiring presidents."
      ],
